{#
    ---
    title: Input Attributes
    ---

    Type: Atoms -> Input

    Description:
        The input attributes pattern provides several standard attributes needed for input fields. This pattern is used in several other Input Atoms.

    Parameters:
        input_attributes_id: Input ID.
        input_attributes_name: Name attribute of the input element.
        input_attributes_placeholder: Placeholder text of the input element.
        input_attributes_type: Input type.
        input_attributes_value: Input default value.
        input_attributes_aria_label: Aria Label for the input field.
        input_attributes_tabindex: Input tabindex attribute.
        input_attributes_disabled: Bool determining if the input is disabled or not. Options: true, false.
        input_attributes_readonly: Bool determining if the input is readonly or not. Options: true, false.
        input_attributes_required: Bool determining if the input is required or not. Options: true, false.

    Last Updated: February 8, 2021
#}

